President Biden has declared a major disaster in Arkansas due to severe storms, straight-line winds, and tornadoes that occurred from June 25 to June 26, 2023. This declaration allows federal assistance to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Mr. Roland W. Jackson from FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the state and based on damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA news desk.